<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa30">
<l>vaṅkak kaṭal kaṭainta mātavaṉai kēcavaṉai</l>
<l>tiṅkaḷ tirumukattu cēyiḻaiyār ceṉṟiṟaiñci</l>
<l>aṅkap paṟai koṇṭa vāṟṟai yaṇi putuvaip</l>
<l>paiṅkamalat taṇ teriyal paṭṭar pirāṉ kōtai coṉṉa</l>
<l>caṅkat tamiḻ mālai muppatum tappāmē</l>
<l>iṅkipparicuraippār īriraṇṭu māl varai tōḷ</l>
<l>ceṅkaṇ tirumukattuc celvat tirumālāl</l>
<l>eṅkum tiruvaruḷ peṟṟiṉpuṟuvar empāvāy.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who recite here, in this manner, without fail,</l>
<l rend="indent">all thirty [verses] of the garland [composed] in classical Tamil</l>
<l rend="indent">spoken by Kōtai—</l>
<l rend="indent">[daughter of] the head among priests</l>
<l rend="indent">with cool garlands of fresh lotuses</l>
<l rend="indent">from the decorated Putuvai—</l>
<l rend="indent">of the way the auspicious, moon-faced, beautiful-jewel-wearing girls</l>
<l rend="indent">obtained that paṟai-drum,</l>
<l rend="indent">having gone there [and]</l>
<l rend="indent">made obeisance to</l>
<l rend="indent">Keśava,</l>
<l rend="indent">Mādhava who churned the sea [with] ship</l>
<l>shall be gratified</l>
<l>obtaining [His] sacred grace everywhere</l>
<l rend="indent">thanks to Tirumāl</l>
<l rend="indent">with red eyes, a beautiful face</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] four big mountain[-like] shoulders.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
